PART 4: EXTERIOR H-DEVIATION — HOW MUCH DOES THE EXTERIOR MATTER?
======================================================================

  For each inner 4-tournament, compute H-variance over 16 exterior configs:
    Average H-variance over exterior: 11.0625
    For comparison, total Var(H) at n=5: 17.8125
    Fraction explained by exterior: 0.6211
    Fraction explained by interior: 0.3789

  The interior (the "Baer subplane") explains 37.9% of the H-variance!
  The exterior (new arcs) contributes only 62.1%.

  This is the TOURNAMENT BAER PRINCIPLE:
  The substructure controls the invariant; the ambient extension is "noise".


